---
title: Open science matters — timeline of the Lancet and New England Journal of Medicine frauds
author: Mostapha Benhenda
date: 2020-06-15
hero: ./images/hortonwho.jpg
excerpt: Lancet and NEJM retractions are good for open science, here's a timeline of events
---


The latest retractions by the Lancet and the New England Journal of Medicine are notable victories for **open science**. These **hoaxes** were more than obscure scientific literature. They had **immediate consequences** on medical practice and policies. These retractions are **not the first scandals** for the [Lancet](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lancet#Controversies) and [NEJM](http://ijme.in/articles/the-new-england-journal-of-medicine-commercial-conflict-of-interest-and-revisiting-the-vioxx-scandal/?galley=html), but they are among the most striking. They exposed in broad daylight what happens **when** **science can’t breathe**.

I prepared **timelines** to better understand the sequence of events, and learn from them. The fraud scheme didn’t start with the Lancet or NEJM publications: earlier, the same gang of fraudsters (Mehra, Patel and Desai) posted an influential **preprint**.

If I forgot something, feel free to ping me on Twitter ([@mostafabenh](https://twitter.com/mostafabenh)), or better, [edit the blog yourself](https://github.com/mostafachatillon/gatsby-theme-novela-example_test/blob/master/content/posts/2020-06-15-timeline/index.mdx) and submit a pull request on GitHub (yes, this blog is open-source).

### Consequences of the frauds

###   

#### The Lancet fraud

###   

-   **22 May**

Publication of the Lancet hoax:

[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*qIrJPobwnVwqiogt.jpeg)](https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(20)31180-6/fulltext)

-   **23 May**

**France** minister of health Olivier Veran requests an emergency review of hydroxychloroquine prescription rules:

[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*xg_5qEXMKOcQ3zl-.png)](https://twitter.com/olivierveran/status/1264145851955458048)



-   **24 May**

In less than 24 hours, the **French High Council for Public Health** ([@HCSP_fr](https://twitter.com/hcsp_fr)) warns against the “**dangers**” of hydroxychloroquine:

[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*qdMDrm_cT070S-rQ.jpeg)](https://www.hcsp.fr/Explore.cgi/avisrapportsdomaine?clefr=837)


-   **25 May**

The **World Health Organization** suspends its hydroxychloroquine clinical trials:


  <iframe  style="margin:0 auto;" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OEH1pamBaEs" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>



-   **26 May**

The **Italian Medicines Agency (AIFA)** suspends authorization of hydroxychloroquine use for Covid-19 outside clinical trials.

[](https://aifa.gov.it/-/aifa-sospende-l-autorizzazione-all-utilizzo-di-idrossiclorochina-per-il-trattamento-del-covid-19-al-di-fuori-degli-studi-clinici)

[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*NjZpblzeObJ-Jbt2.jpeg)](https://aifa.gov.it/-/aifa-sospende-l-autorizzazione-all-utilizzo-di-idrossiclorochina-per-il-trattamento-del-covid-19-al-di-fuori-degli-studi-clinici)

-   **29 May**

The **United States** terminates relationship with WHO. The Lancet fraud is not officially mentioned, but the **coincidence is striking**, because the Lancet fraud was massively denounced and retweeted by Trump MAGA fans, but still ignored by WHO (see in particular this tweet by [@arkancideisreal](https://twitter.com/Arkancideisreal/status/1264032084944814082) on 23 May to the White House Press Secretary). 
For Trump, that was a unique window of opportunity for a controversial decision.



  <iframe  style="margin:0 auto;" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/3j8N_rD7Eug" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>



-   **11 June**

The **Massachusetts Institute of Technology** terminates relationship with **Elsevier** publisher (Lancet owner). The MIT doesn’t mention the latest Lancet fraud, but again, the timing is remarkable.

[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*31temrd-ZJ9dD0gb.jpeg)](http://news.mit.edu/2020/guided-by-open-access-principles-mit-ends-elsevier-negotiations-0611)

### The preprint fraud

###   

The first hoax was **not peer-reviewed**. Nevertheless, this preprint had significant [impact on public health](https://www.isglobal.org/en/healthisglobal/-/custom-blog-portlet/ivermectin-and-covid-19-how-a-flawed-database-shaped-the-covid-19-response-of-several-latin-american-countries/2877257/0) in **Paraguay, Peru** and **Bolivia**.

-   **6 April**

**First posting** of the preprint on SSRN server (incidentally, SSRN is owned by Elsevier, like the Lancet). It has been withdrawn from SSRN server since then, but the latest version (19 April) is still [available here](http://www.proyectodime.info/documents/219/Utilidad_de_la_ivermectina.pdf). 

Grainger and Mehra are also co-authors of this hoax.

[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*dyos-1pFJwNkRv_x.jpeg)](http://www.proyectodime.info/documents/219/Utilidad_de_la_ivermectina.pdf)

-   **7 April**

**Paraguay** minister of health, Julio Mazzoleni, restricts sale of **ivermectin**  to **prevent shortages**.

[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*GElo172izlN1XfmH.jpeg)](https://twitter.com/jc_portillo/status/1248060739912335360)

-   **2 May**

[Gustavo Aguirre Chang,](https://www.linkedin.com/in/gustavo-aguirre-chang-5626535b?originalSubdomain=pe) doctor from the San Pablo hospital complex in Lima, Peru, releases a white paper (non peer-reviewed) recommending **ivermectin** to be included in the national COVID-19 treatment guidelines of **Peru**.

[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*doDbrPoG8bbNgAW1.jpeg)](https://www.megalabs.global/ivermectina-en-la-primera-linea-de-accion-terapeutica-para-covid-19/)


-   **8 May**

**Peru** minister of health, Victor Zamora Mesia, requests the **inclusion of ivermectin**:

[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*BzxF5tVt6xcar0Xk.jpeg)](https://cdn.www.gob.pe/uploads/document/file/694719/RM_270-2020-MINSA.PDF)

-   **12 May**

**Bolivia** minister of health Marcelo Navajas also **includes ivermectin** in the treatment of patients with coronavirus (COVID-19), under medical protocol and informed consent (**without approval)**.



  <iframe  style="margin:0 auto;" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/KeHdSr9qkpM" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>



-   **13 May**

**Large queues** to buy ivermectin in Santa Cruz, **Bolivia**


  <iframe  style="margin:0 auto;" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/K7m9JnnIoPQ" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>



-   **16 May**

In Trinidad-Beni, **Bolivia**, distribution campaign of **350,000 ivermectin doses** to the population



  <iframe  style="margin:0 auto;" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/4qf3mIbT0fA" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

### The New England Journal of Medicine fraud

###   

The impact of the NEJM fraud is harder to assess at the moment. Authors conclude a “confirmation” that blood pressure drugs angiotensin-converting–enzyme (ACE) inhibitors and angiotensin-receptor blockers (ARBs) were not harmful in the Covid-19 clinical context. It still harmed patients by giving them a **false sense of security**:


[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*Zu0qhl6FbRR2c-y4.png)](https://twitter.com/PavelTomancak/status/1256267162022371328)


[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*JA7QYDFO6Ic3eYkT.png)](https://twitter.com/Will_A_Huang/status/1256276684166201344)



[![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/0*i9p6bc1BzNLc_31N.png)](https://twitter.com/JoeBeOne/status/1257099316465938432)


